BGP is used to advertise Kubernetes cluster service for LAN access, while pod ip addresses are not advertised, so all traffic targeting cluster service must go through the router.

p.font: Q: Why not use local storage in Kubernetes?

A: The cluster might be migrated to cloud some day when we actually need public access, and if we use native local storage, we need to backup everything with solutions like `restic` and restore them carefully with exactly same node setup, which is complicated and error prone. TrueNAS provides a secure (hardened) environment, and capable of handling a lot of local storage service, when we migrate, we just need to import whole ZFS storage to cloud.
Q: Where can I find these projects?

A: Every product listed in this diagram is free open source software, you can click on it, some will navigate you to the chart repo (which generates the deployment manifest), and some to the source repo. Usually you can find a link to its source repo in that chart repo.
BTW, If you are interested in more details or have any question about this diagram, please feel free to email me at `me@arhat.dev`
